In response to attribution of recent climate change, the City of Melbourne, in 2002, set a target to reduce carbon emissions to net zero by 2020 and to carbon-neutral by 2050. A carbon market programme was implemented that allowed landowners on all Melbourne’s public land to create and trade carbon credit units through the ClimateWorks Marketplace. In 2008 this was replaced by the Victorian Environment Network, which encouraged farmers to contribute towards carbon conservation through a series of carbon conservation programs.

